{"cursor":"30684","size":15,"audio":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Uplifting_Trance_Sidechain.ogg"],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Dynamic range compression', also called 'DRC' (often seen in DVD and car CD\nplayer settings) or simply 'compression' reduces the volume of loud sounds or\namplifies quiet sounds by narrowing or \"compressing\" an audio signal's dynamic\nrange. Compression is commonly used in sound recording and reproduction and\nbroadcasting.\n\nThe dedicated electronic hardware unit or audio software used to apply\ncompression is called a compressor. Compressors often have 'attack' and\n'release' controls that vary the rate at which compression is applied and smooth\nthe effect.\n","linknr":383,"url":"Dynamic_range_compression","recorded":1362484258,"links":59,"instances":["audio_signal_processing","software","computing","audio","disambiguation","recorded_music","recording_ltd","audio","disambiguation","audio"],"pdf":["http://tech.ebu.ch/docs/r/r128.pdf","http://tech.ebu.ch/docs/tech/tech3341.pdf","http://tech.ebu.ch/docs/tech/tech3342.pdf","http://ccrma.stanford.edu/courses/192b/192b_Lecture_1_06.pdf","http://www.uaudio.com/_works/pdf/manuals/LA-2A_manual.pdf","http://www.rane.com/pdf/ranenotes/Dynamics_Processors.pdf","http://www.rane.com/pdf/ranenotes/Dynamics_Processors.pdf","http://web.archive.org/web/20101231072136/http://www.tcelectronic.com/media/droney_massey_2001_compres.pdf","http://www.tcelectronic.com/media/droney_massey_2001_compres.pdf","http://web.archive.org/web/20101231072136/http://www.tcelectronic.com/media/droney_massey_2001_compres.pdf"],"categories":["Audio engineering","Dynamics processing"],"headings":["Types","Design","Compressor controls and features","Use","Limiting","Side-chaining","Parallel compression","{{visible anchor|Multiband compression}}","Serial compression","Common uses","Other uses","Compressors for software audio players","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikim